	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-steve-o odd alt depth-2" id="li-comment-493223">
		<div class="commentBackgroundizer">
			<div class="commentLiner" id="comment-493223">
				<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/c10a49c10c223c507d5284f7eecde8d0?s=50&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.marksdailyapple.com%2Fwordpress%2Fwp-content%2Fthemes%2FmarksDailyApple%2Fimages%2FgrokGravatar.png%3Fs%3D50&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-50 photo' height='50' width='50' />				<div class="commentContent">
										<p>Fast food is a volume sales business. It is also much less expensive for a company to target its existing customers than to try and get new customers.</p>
<p>This is simply a ploy to get some of its existing customers to consume much more of its food.</p>
<p>I love when people talk about eating fast food &#8220;in moderation&#8221;. What they don&#8217;t understand is the fast food model is not about moderation. They want you to consume as much as possible as frequently as possible.</p>
<p>No higher end restaurant expects you to eat their food for every meal every day of the week, but that is the goal of fast food.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="clearMe"></div>
			</div>
